A semi join keeps only the rows from the first table (x) that have a matching value in the second table (y) based on the join keys.
semi_join(flights, airlines, by = "carrier")
This returns only the flights whoose carrier exists in the airlines table.

Anti Join (anti_join)
An anti join keeps only the rows from the first table (x) that do NOT have a matching value in the second table (y).
anti_join(flights, airlines, by = "carrier")
this rertusn flights whoose carrier code is not found in airlines.




